      "system": {
        "tags": [],
        "description": "<p>At <strong data-start=\"933\" data-end=\"946\">9th level</strong>, a Magic-User can begin crafting <strong data-start=\"980\" data-end=\"995\">magic items</strong>, but only items <strong data-start=\"1012\" data-end=\"1037\">usable by Magic-Users</strong>. The process involves:</p><ul data-start=\"1063\" data-end=\"1433\"><li data-start=\"1063\" data-end=\"1165\">Gathering rare materials related to the item's magic (e.g., dragon scales for fire resistance)</li><li data-start=\"1166\" data-end=\"1226\">Spending time and gold to craft and enchant the item</li><li data-start=\"1227\" data-end=\"1311\">A base cost of 500 gp per spell level for items that duplicate spell effects</li><li data-start=\"1312\" data-end=\"1433\">A 15% minimum chance of failure, determined at the end of the process​</li></ul><p data-start=\"1435\" data-end=\"1739\">Scrolls and potions are the easiest to create, while more powerful items require <strong data-start=\"1516\" data-end=\"1534\">months of work</strong> and possibly special rituals. The <strong data-start=\"1569\" data-end=\"1607\">DM may set additional requirements</strong> for powerful magic items, such as needing a specific location or celestial alignment​.</p>",
