    {
      "_originalKey": "!actors.items!GCVeG8fxZwX1Gzw4.O60iO2lcKTrDPaso",
      "name": "Arcane Spellcasting",
      "type": "specialAbility",
      "img": "systems/fantastic-depths/assets/img/item/specialAbility.png",
      "system": {
        "tags": [],
        "description": "<p data-start=\"31\" data-end=\"347\">Magic-Users harness arcane energy through <strong data-start=\"73\" data-end=\"115\">intense study and careful memorization</strong> of spells recorded in their spellbooks. Unlike Clerics, who receive divine magic, Magic-Users must <strong data-start=\"215\" data-end=\"244\">prepare spells in advance</strong> by studying their books each day. Once a spell is cast, it is erased from memory until re-memorized.</p><p data-start=\"349\" data-end=\"650\">Magic-Users have a limited selection of spells they can prepare per day, increasing as they gain levels. Their spells range from minor utilities such as <em data-start=\"502\" data-end=\"514\">Read Magic</em> to devastating attacks like <em data-start=\"543\" data-end=\"553\">Fireball</em> and reality-warping incantations at higher levels​.</p><p data-start=\"652\" data-end=\"841\" data-is-last-node=\"\">Because of their reliance on spellbooks, Magic-Users must protect and expand their libraries, seeking out <strong data-start=\"758\" data-end=\"804\">lost tomes, scrolls, and ancient knowledge</strong> to improve their magical repertoire.</p>",
