    {
      "_originalKey": "!actors.items!GCVeG8fxZwX1Gzw4.W4Ra8QX140MWSDNj",
      "name": "Summon Undead",
      "type": "specialAbility",
      "system": {
        "description": "<p>Either type of lich can summon other powerful undead for aid. The summons can be made simply by concentrating, and the creature(s) responding arrive [[/r 1d100 #rounds]] <strong>rounds</strong> later, depending on their distance. The summons may be made as often as desired, but any one type of creature will respond only once per day at most. To randomly determine the creatures appearing in response to the summons, roll [[/r 1d20 #See lich summon table for result]] and refer to the table. Roll again if a type of creature has already responded that day.</p><table style=\"width:300px\"><tbody><tr><th><p>Roll</p></th><th><p>Creature</p></th></tr><tr><td><p>1-5</p></td><td><p>Spectre ([[/r 2d4 #Spectre]])</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6-9</p></td><td><p>Vampire ([[/r 1d6 #Vampire]])</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10-12</p></td><td><p>Phantom, Shade ([[/r 1d3 #Phantom, Shade]])</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13-15</p></td><td><p>Haunt, Ghost ([[/r 1d2 #Chaotic Haunt,Ghost]] Chaotic)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>Haunt, Poltergeist ([[/r 1d2 #Haunt, Poltergeist]])</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>Spirit, Druj</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>Spirit, Revenant</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>Nightshade (any 1)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>Undead Beholder</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>A summoned vampire may have a [[/r 1d100 #Summoned vampire is a magic-user or cleric on 25 or less. Roll for each]]<strong> </strong>chance (check for each) of being a magic-user or cleric of level 7-9 ([[/r 1d3 + 6 #Level]]).</p>",
